ian greens, cut into pieces"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"50 g broccolini, cut into thirds"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 tbsp honey"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 tsp sesame oil"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"4 fresh mushrooms, cut into slices"}],"nutrition":["per 1 portion","2408 kJ \/ 573 kcal","62 g","28 g","23 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["<b>Recipe for one: <b>cook both duck breasts and use the leftovers in soup, noodles or salad.","Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em> or the <em>Everyday Cookbook<\/em> for the Vegetable stock paste recipe.","Substitute soy sauce with tamari for a gluten free option.","Place any uncooked duck breast into the refrigerator and use as a substitute to the pork  in <em>Pork San Choy Bau<\/em>.<b><br><b>"],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","45m","2 portions"]}